article.description: Foster Sawyer and Jake Blumrick combined to throw for 223 yards to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 20-10 victory over Abilene Christian in Southland Conference action on Saturday night.
article.headline: Stephen F. Austin eases past Abilene Christian 20-10
article.linkText: Stephen F. Austin eases past Abilene Christian 20-10
article.story: ABILENE, Texas -- Foster Sawyer and Jake Blumrick combined to throw for 223 yards to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 20-10 victory over Abilene Christian in Southland Conference action on Saturday night. Sawyer was 11-of-20 passing for 113 yards with one touchdown and Blumrick threw for 110 yards on 14-of-25 passing. The Lumberjacks (2-2, 2-0 Southland Conference) had four takeaways on the night to thwart Abilene Christian (1-3, 1-1). Alize Ward, who returned a game-winning interception 70 yards against Incarnate Word last week, picked off one against the Wildcats. Lawrence Ghansah also had an interception. ACU also lost two fumbles. Sawyer threw a 12-yard scoring pass to Frank Iheanacho for a 7-3 lead in the first quarter. Storm Ruiz added field goals of 35- and 27-yards to go up 13-3 in the third quarter. Kijana Amous ran in from the 5 for an insurance score. Dallas Sealey led ACU, throwing for 179 yards and one score. --- More AP college football: http://collegefootball.ap.org and http://www.twitter.com/AP-Top25
